    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-chilli-and-sage-pork-shoulder-and-creamy-mushroom-stew/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based <strong>hob-safe</strong> <strong>oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a matching lid with a little drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced pork shoulder </strong>with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until lightly browned</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-chilli-and-sage-pork-shoulder-and-creamy-mushroom-stew/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Chop your <strong>chestnut mushrooms </strong>roughly</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-chilli-and-sage-pork-shoulder-and-creamy-mushroom-stew/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pork is slightly browned, reduce the heat to medium and add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>with your<strong> chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>dried sage </strong>and <strong>chopped mushrooms</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>stock mix </strong>with your<strong> Chinese rice wine </strong>and 350ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[450ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cover with the lid and put the dish in the oven for 55 min or until the sauce has thickened and the pork is cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>stew</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-chilli-and-sage-pork-shoulder-and-creamy-mushroom-stew/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potato </strong>to a baking tray with a large piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> (or two!), then drizzle over a large splash of <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Scrunch the foil around the potato to form a tightly sealed parcel</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4 or more? Make 2 separate parcels!</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 55 min or until the potato is tender</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-chilli-and-sage-pork-shoulder-and-creamy-mushroom-stew/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-chilli-and-sage-pork-shoulder-and-creamy-mushroom-stew/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the stew is ready, remove the dish from the oven and add your <strong>double cream</strong> with <strong>half </strong>your <strong>chopped parsley </strong>(save some for a garnish!) and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>,<strong> </strong>then return the dish to the oven, uncovered, for 2-3 min or until thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>chilli & sage pork shoulder and creamy mushroom stew</strong></p><p>Once the potatoes are tender, remove the tray from the oven and transfer the <strong>cooked potato </strong>to a heatproof bowl with a small knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>, then crush lightly with a fork \u2013 these are your <strong>buttery crushed potatoes</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-chilli-and-sage-pork-shoulder-and-creamy-mushroom-stew/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> chilli & sage pork shoulder and creamy mushroom stew</strong> and<strong> </strong>garnish with <strong>remaining chopped parsley</strong></p><p>Serve the<strong> buttery crushed potatoes</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
